article.headline: Ark.-Little Rock 108, St. Gregory's 58
article.story: LITTLE ROCK, Ark. -- Arkansas-Little Rock had eight players score in double figures and shot 59 percent from the field Wednesday in a 108-58 rout of St. Gregory's. The Trojans (2-1) jumped out to an 18-1 lead and increased it to 60-26 by halftime. Little Rock hit 45 of 76 shots from the field, outrebounded St. Gregory's 52-32 and held a 60-10 advantage on points in the paint. Matt Mouzy had 16 points for Little Rock, Eric Kibi 14 and Marlon Louzeiro 13. Solomon Bozeman, Reggie Sonnier, Montrell Thornton and Courtney Jackson added 11 each, and Daylon Guy had 10. Guy nearly had a triple-double off the bench with nine rebounds and eight assists in 21 minutes. Fayzon Richey had 25 points for St. Gregory's, which shot 27 percent from the field (17 for 63) and committed 19 turnovers. The game counted as an exhibition for the Cavaliers, an NAIA school that was 3-1 coming into the game.
